        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 5:00PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 30
miles northwest of Nordman, or 53 miles west of Bonners Ferry, moving
north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Metaline Falls and Metaline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
